  "prompt": "Which type of energy produce by steam?",
  "response": "Steam is used to produce mechanical and electrical energy through various processes:\n\n1. Mechanical Energy:\n- Steam engines\n- Steam turbines\n- Reciprocating steam engines\n\n2. Electrical Energy:\n- Steam turbine generators in power plants\n- Thermal power stations\n- Nuclear power plants\n- Geothermal power plants\n- Concentrated solar power plants\n\nSteam is heated to high temperatures and pressures, which drives turbines connected to generators, converting thermal energy into electrical energy through mechanical rotation.\n\nThe main steps in steam energy production are:\n- Water is heated to create steam\n- Steam is directed at turbine blades\n- Turbine rotation drives an electrical generator\n- Generator produces electricity\n\nDifferent heat sources can be used to generate steam:\n- Coal\n- Natural gas\n- Nuclear fission\n- Solar energy\n- Geothermal heat\n\nSteam energy is an important method of electricity generation worldwide, accounting for a significant portion of global power production.",
